cs.CV, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.MM, cs.IR 

The paper deals with computer vision and machine learning techniques for fine-grained recognition, specifically focusing on pooling strategies for feature encoding. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition). The paper also introduces a novel way to visualize decisions made by these approaches, which involves analyzing the influence of semantic parts, indicating a possible connection to multimodal learning (cs.MM). The paper also discusses the use of machine learning techniques for learning the pooling strategy during training, which falls under the category of artificial intelligence (cs.AI). Finally, the paper discusses the performance of the proposed approach on standard datasets, which suggests a possible connection to information retrieval (cs.IR).
